annotationA: Tumor necrosis factor receptor-associated factor 6 belongs to a family of adaptor proteins involved in transducing downstream signaling by interacting with cell surface receptors. It mediates the pro-inflammatory effects of Toll and related receptor signaling, and the egr-induced JNK activation that induces cell death
annotationB: Tak1-like 2; Protein kinase activity; ATP binding; protein serine/threonine kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: protein phosphorylation
